avro-c
------------------------------------------
Apache Avro is a data serialization system.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.17-1
  libjansson4-2.4-1bl1
  liblzma-devel-5.0.2_20110517-1
  liblzma5-5.0.2_20110517-1
  zlib-devel-1.2.7-1
  zlib0-1.2.7-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.23.51-1
  cmake-2.8.9-2
  cygport-0.11.3-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://avro.apache.org/

Canonical download:
  http://ftp.tsukuba.wide.ad.jp/software/apache/avro/avro-1.7.4/c/avro-c-1.7.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack avro-c-1.7.4-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
         unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./avro-c-1.7.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/avro-c-1.7.4-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/avro-c-1.7.4-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libavro22.0.0-1.7.4-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libavro-devel-1.7.4-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(avro-c)
  /usr/bin/avroappend.exe
  /usr/bin/avrocat.exe
  /usr/bin/avromod.exe
  /usr/bin/avropipe.exe
